	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have found that this is a wonderful hybrid class (warrior/cleric).  Paladins really shine when they gain the ability to cast spells - level 9 - which will allow you heal beyond using Lay Hands.  Ah, Lay Hands. . . this is the mainstay of the Paladin class.  I have found this to be most useful when fleeing for your life, as it may buy you the time you need to find guards or cross a zone boundary when being chased by a foe or foes.<BR>
<BR>
Another wonderful thing about Paladins is that they are unrestricted in their use of armor, and can use all types of weapons except for piercing and long range.  While not as tough as warriors, Paladins can still stand in combat for extended periods of time.  This character works well either when fighting alone or when in a group.  Paladins also gain some combat skills, such as Bash at level 9, and these will help augment a Paladin's capacity to inflict damage.  Overall, my experience is that this is a very well-rounded character.<BR>
<BR>
Bear in mind that the Paladin has chosen to live a life of honor and duty, and that s/he is an example to others of these qualities.  A Paladin does not willingly align him/herself with nefarious or unsavory individuals.  If you play within the bounds of this class - offering healing and assistance to others in need - you will have a great time playing this class and make a lot of friends in the process.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
