				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(10,3329);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >10</font></a></b>
				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Paladins:  Now that they can use bows, I gather this is new from<BR>
the responses, someone raised the question of why they wouldn't be able<BR>
to.  It's not a physical disability or bad eyesight.  It's a choice of<BR>
honor.  A Paladin considers a bow the same way real people consider<BR>
a drive-by shooting: an act of cowardice.  If you can't stand and<BR>
face your enemy and put your skill against his or her own, then you<BR>
do not deserve the honor of being a Paladin.<BR>
<BR>
Just for the record, I use a bow though I can never find enough bloody arrows.<BR>
<BR>
Thraash
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
